H0.text: Blinking is a behavior that humans learn, not an innate skill, because humans are born knowing some things and learn others, as Monica understood.

H1.text: Breathing is a behavior that humans learn, as Monica learned that humans are born knowing some things and learn others.

H2.text: Crying is a behavior humans learn.

H3.text: Swimming is a behavior that humans learn, rather than an ability that they are born with.

A4.text: Eyeblink conditioning is a form of motor learning, indicating that blinking can be learned through training.

A5.text: Motor learning can calibrate simple movements like reflexes, indicating that some reflexive behaviors are learned through training.
